Parliament, Tuesday, 29 May 2018 – The Portfolio Committee on Justice and Correctional Services will tomorrow be briefed by the Department of Justice and Constitutional Development on the Prevention and Combating of Hate Crimes and Hate Speech Bill. The committee will also be briefed on the International Crimes Bill. Details are as follows: 
	Date: Wednesday, 30 May 2018
	Time:  10:00, Second Floor, Marks Building.
	Venue: Committee Room 1, Ground Floor, 120 Plein Street Building. ISSUED BY PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSONS OF THE JOINT CONSTITUTIONAL REVIEW COMMITTEE For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairpersons, please contact the committee’s Media Officer: Name: Rajaa Azzakani (Ms)Tel: 021 403 8437Cell: 081 703 9542E-mail: razzakani@parliament.gov.za The Bill of Rights guarantees the right to assemble, demonstrate, picket and present petitions as long as this is done in a peaceful way and the protesters are unarmed.Read more